    "{i}Sigurd was used to spend time in saunas back in Sweden, so visiting Japanese onsens wasn't too far off."
    "{i}The customs, the hygiene rules and so on, he could perfectly apply them and not stand out too much, especially for elders who would give him stares."
    "{i}He was tall, and not very Japanese looking, so these old grandpas were expecting him to disrespect the sacred silence of their precious hot springs."
    "{i}This time Kaisei joined him. It was a rare sight to see the silver kitsune get down from his sanctuary, let alone bathe in public."
    "{i}Though today, for some reason, it was mostly the two of them together."
    "{i}There was a group of elderly men, who looked like they had stayed all morning in the onsen, before leaving Sigurd and Kaisei alone.{/i}"

