    "The two men were sitting in the warm water in silence."
    "It was a rather small hot spring, surrounded by massive rocks and soft light coming from the red paper lanterns."
    "Not only the water and steam were warm, but the whole onsen was welcoming and could soothe the heart of the coldest man in this world. This sense of privacy and secrecy were most certainly effective for this atmosphere to work."
    "Who knew if it was because of the size of it or its popularity, but one would rarely find anyone bathing here, which was exactly what Kaisei was searching for."
    "The silver fox had explained a few rules to the dragon, but upon seeing that he was much more experienced in the matter, he left him be."
    "Kaisei was tense at first. It had been long since he last stepped into an onsen."
    'Especially with an acquaintance he had just met. Though would he qualify Sigurd as only an "acquaintance" now ? How long had it actually been again ?'
    "Maybe less than a year ? But nowadays, even the shortest of the month can feel like the longest. Right, they felt like they’ve known each other for much longer than whatever reality could tell."
    "So their proximity grew as well, along with this silly curiosity animating the slight tension between them."
    "It was much less obvious with the kitsune, but the tall ashen-blond man was definitely interested in this mysterious person."
    "What to not be curious about him ? He was residing in a secluded shrine, far from humanity, and rarely talked about himself. Not even Ryo or Opal could tell without hesitation his favourite food."
    "So this blessed instant, where both men were stripped to their most simple settings, was the perfect moment to get to know each other. However, silence was vital in an onsen."
    "It wasn’t prohibited to talk, but these places were of use for meditation and relaxation. So trivial conversations would be the number one enemy for one’s meditation."
    "Both of them knew that perfectly well, and remained shut for long enough. It was peaceful, not the kind of silence where someone wonders if they should say something to fight the uneasiness." 
    "Only the sound of the water gently caressing against the rocks sang in their ears."
    "That, and their soft breathing when they focused enough to hear it. Both men were slowly inhaling the steam, and exhaling from their nose in a faint sigh."
    "This act only felt almost intimate, when hearing so closely. The dragon felt almost soothed from the kitsune’s breathing."
    "What would his heartbeat sound like ?"
    "What would his honest laugh ring like ?"
    "So many questions to fill this tranquil void."
    "Sigurd got lost in his own fantasy, while the silver fox thought about one thing: nothing. No insignificant thoughts to run in circles in his head."
    "At last, now, was he permitted to relax. It wasn't his duties at the shrine that would make his shoulders stiff, but the visitors."
    "It was a rare thing to see new faces in a Shinto shrine, especially young ones. But all this energy spent in talking to them and looking after their every move to assure that they wouldn't misbehave..."
    "It all tired Kaisei to his core. So this little escape was more helpful than he would admit."

